description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for an exceptional individual to join the NCA Radiology Senior Management Team as the Radiology Operations Manager.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a new NCA wide role covering all care organisations which will monitor operational delivery of key targets, KPIs and capacity planning, as the direct link between our individual clinical service leads, Service Managers and our Business Intelligence team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will also assume responsibility for management, coordination and development of all administrative and booking functions across our services which make up the Directorate (Radiology, NES Neurophysiology and Clinical Photography).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Directorate is undergoing significant change at this time in order to build a platform to sustain delivery of exceptional quality services and progress many of the key transformation projects which will see delivery of services in ways we have not seen previously.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you excel with a challenge, wish to develop and have a passion for continuous improvement we want to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Recent experience and knowledge of Imaging Diagnostic services and systems is required for this role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In line with the Trust’s Single Equality Scheme we welcome applications from everyone irrespective of ethnic origin, disability, age, gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, disability, nationality, religion, marital status, social back ground or trade union membership. However, as members of ethnicity minority groups and individuals with disabilities are currently under-represented at this level of post, we would encourage applications from members of these groups. Appointment will be based on merit alone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;David O’Brien&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Director of Radiology Services, Neurophysiology (NES) &amp; Clinical Photography&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;David.OBrien2@srht.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mobile – 07729626036&lt;/p&gt;
